 # Library Management API
 A full-stack library management system for managing books. The backend is built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB.


# Features
CRUD Operations: Manage books in the library.
Validation: Input validation using Joi.
MongoDB Integration: Persist data with MongoDB.


# Tech Stack
Node.js
Express
MongoDB & Mongoose
Joi for validation

# Installation

1. Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/library-management.git
cd library-management

2. Install dependencies:
npm install

3. Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory with the following variables:

LIBRARY_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster.mongodb.net/<dbname>
PORT=3002

# Running the Application
Start the server: "npm run dev"
The server will run at http://localhost:3002.

# API Endpoints

POST "/library" - Add a new book
POST "/author" - Add a new author
POST "/review" - Add review

GET "/library" - Get all books
GET "/author" - Get all authors
GET "/review" - Get all reviews

GET "/books/:id" - Get a book by ID
GET "/author/:id" - Get an author by ID
GET "/review/:id" - Get review by ID

PATCH "/library/:id" - Update a book by ID
PATCH "/author/:id" - Update a author by ID
PATCH "/review/:id" - Update a review by ID

DELETE "/library/:id" - Delete a book by ID
DELETE "/author/:id" - Delete a author by ID
DELETE "/review/:id" - Delete a review by ID



